title: For Sale:  IWI Desert Eagle
postcontent: Desert Eagle IWI Israel has had a reputation for producing excellent weaponry for extensive and active military use. The iconic Desert Eagle was one of their first production runs of a potential sidearm for select elements of the Israeli military and Shin Bet, their military intelligence service. After a few years of service, the gun design was retired in favor of the more versatile Jericho pistol. However, the Desert Eagle is still an extremely sought after firearm. In recent years, production was sold to Magnum Research for stateside manufacturing making Israeli made versions the "white whale" of the gun industry. This particular firearm is such a gun!

title: For Sale:  Italian-made Beretta 92FS INOX
postcontent: Hard to find these days, the stainless Italian-made (Gardone Val Trompia) Beretta 92FS INOX (inoxidizable). This one is a 1994... the last year before the Clinton "foreign import" ban kicked in. They started producing these in the U.S. after that, but were never the same. The US version had polymer and polymer-coated parts and they sported black controls. The Italian version also features a molded "wraparound" grip with finger grooves that wasn't commonly used on the US models. The Bruniton finish on the aluminum frame is basically flawless and the gun has a low round count (500 from the original owner, 50 from me).I've held onto it for years because it's a really nice pistol, but I never liked the fatness of the double-stack grip and have moved on to 1911's. It's just sat in a safe for years now, so might as well let it go and free up space for something that I will actually shoot. Not a motivated seller... so the $600 price tag is firm. Includes the original marked "Made in Italy"  Beretta case and both original 15-round factory mags.Buyer must have a CCW or valid purchase permit, with matching ID.
